doc.after: Hillcourt retired from the BSA on August 1, 1965. In 1971, he and Grace finally completed the world tour he had started in 1926; along the way they attended the 13th World Scout Jamboree in Fujinomiya, Japan. Grace Hillcourt died in 1973.[5] Rather than live alone, Bill moved into the home of his good friends Carson and Martha Buck.
